Newly corrected, this highly acclaimed text is suitable for advanced physics courses. The authors present a very accessible macroscopic view of classical electromagnetics that emphasizes integrating electromagnetic theory with physical optics. The survey follows the historical development of physics, culminating in the use of four-vector relativity to fully integrate electricity with magnetism. Corrected and emended reprint of the Brooks/Cole Thomson Learning, 1994, third edition.
